Rating: 4
This recipe is a favorite. Easy to make, and very tasty, not too sweet, with a nice crispy top (at least when they're fresh. If you store the leftovers the tops soften up.). I usually make the mistake of mixing in all of the crystallized ginger from the ingredients list, instead of half of it, but the flavor doesn't suffer at all. I've never bothered with the glaze. Particularly when made in giant muffin cups, these are so filling they don't need any more sweetness! Highly recommended as a fall and winter breakfast staple.

