Rating: 4
This is one of our fall favorites, and tastes a little more strongly (but not in a bad way) if you use black strap molasses instead of light). I replace 1 1/4 of the flour with whole wheat. 1/2 the oil with apple sauce, and 1/2 tsp. of the ginger with pumpkin pie spice. I also add a an extra 1/4 cup of crystalized ginger chips than called for and skip the glaze. Great with dried cranberries in them too.

Rating: 4
Just made these muffins and we love them. A few changes: roasted butternut squash instead of pumpkin, organic whole wheat flour, and some cinnamon. Delicious!

Rating: 4
This was a great recipe. I omitted the crystallized ginger and added 1/2 tsp of cinnamon and 1/4 tsp of ground cloves. Instead of the glaze, I made some cream cheese frosting. I also made mini-muffins which took about 15 minutes to bake. Served them at Thanksgiving and they were a hit!

Rating: 3
Rather a nice cake than a muffin, but a good cake. I used half rye flour and cut the oil in half, subbing 1/4 c applesauce instead. Added fresh cranberries at the end for some zing and to counteract the sweetness, and sprinkled a crisp topping (oats-flour-sugar-butter) over the top for some crunch. Even with the reduced oil and increased fiber, I got a lovely, springy, super-moist cake. Not pumpkin-tasting, true: but is anything, really? It all tastes like the spices in the end, in my opinion. ; )

Rating: 3
